# grapher_table_smoke.numos — open Grapher, commit y=x, switch to the Table tab,
# screenshot the value table, and ASSERT Grapher is active.
#
# Phase 8L smoke (warning-only candidate; NO golden, NO mask in this phase).
# Exercises the Table tab after committing a simple plottable function. Unlike the
# Graph tab (Phase 8I, whose first replot is deferred), the Table tab renders
# SYNCHRONOUSLY: switchTab(Tab::TABLE) un-hides the sticky header + scrollable panel,
# picks the first valid function, and calls rebuildTable() right away
# (GrapherApp.cpp:812-821, rebuildTable GrapherApp.cpp:2022-2092). So `key table`
# alone populates the table — no flush key is needed.
#
# The committed function y=x is required because GraphModel only treats an
# expression as a valid function if it contains "=" (getExprRHS, GraphModel.cpp:
# 28-36); bare "x" commits invalid and the table's f-column would show "--".
#
# What this captures: the Table tab on its default window — a sticky header row
# ("x" and "f1(x)", GrapherApp.cpp:2050-2058) over a zebra-striped value table whose
# x column starts at _tblStart=-5 with step 1 and whose f1(x) column is the evaluated
# y=x value (rebuildTable GrapherApp.cpp:2070-2086). All cells are pure numbers (%.4g
# / %.6g / "--") and the headers are space-free, so the Table tab has NO stix_math_18
# no-space tofu — no GrapherApp label change was needed in this phase.
#
# Determinism: run1-vs-run2 from fresh launches is byte-identical (the numeric table
# body is fully deterministic on the same binary). As with every emulator screen, the
# only wall-clock-volatile region is the StatusBar clock (HH:MM).
#
# All key tokens are already scriptable (NativeHal scriptNameToKeyCode: down, enter,
# y, =, x, table) — no NativeHal change is required.
#
# Timing notes (deterministic, step-ms 16):
#   * 200 frames -> splash done; launcher.
#   *  60 frames -> Grapher load + fade settles.
#   *   6 keys   -> commit y=x (down, enter, y, =, x, enter).
#   *  80 frames -> expression committed/settled.
#   *   1 key    -> table (switchTab(Tab::TABLE) -> synchronous rebuildTable()).
#   * 150 frames -> table render + screen settles.
#
# Run:
#   program --headless --deterministic --script tests/emulator/scripts/grapher_table_smoke.numos \
#           --frames 800 --screenshot out/grapher_table_smoke.ppm --quiet
# Exit codes: 0 ok · 2 script/parse error · 3 screenshot write error · 4 assertion failure.

log "grapher_table_smoke: waiting for launcher"
wait 200

# Open Grapher (emulator launchApp id 1 — same id as the launcher's Grapher card).
open_app Grapher
wait 60

# Commit the plottable function y=x into the first slot. Sequence:
#   down  : TAB_BAR -> CONTENT (Add row, _numFuncs=0)
#   enter : addFunction() -> startEditing() slot 0
#   y = x : insertVariable('y'), insertVariable('='), insertVariable('x')
#   enter : commit -> stopEditing(); function parsed and marked valid
key down
key enter
key y
key =
key x
key enter
wait 80

# Switch to the Table tab (global shortcut -> switchTab(Tab::TABLE) -> rebuildTable()).
key table
wait 150

# Screenshot FIRST: the deferred capture happens on this frame, before the assert
# runs on a later frame, so the artifact is produced even if the assertion fails.
screenshot out/grapher_table_smoke.ppm
log "grapher_table_smoke: screenshot captured"

assert_app Grapher
log "grapher_table_smoke: assertion passed (Grapher active, Table tab)"
